race.comment: JESSICA RABBIT (4) tried hard in a good maiden on debut at Ballarat which prompted the stable to test the waters at Group 3 level, which she struggled in at Caulfield. This is far easier, she lands in a good spot and goes close. MYSTERY 'N' DRAMA (7) ran a good race when settling for second here first up on wet ground. She showed some promise last time in and should be fitter now for a suitable rise in trip. SOMERSAULT (10) made good improvement at her second start when just nosed out at Kyneton. She draws softly and can make another step. PINOT FOR MIKE (8) was big odds on debut here but ran well in a bunched finish, getting home nicely. She'll get further but will be better for that run and has claims.
